# How to Run SkillNet — Complete Step-by-Step Guide

## Prerequisites

| Tool | Required For | Check Command |
|------|-------------|---------------|
| Node.js 20+ | Manual method | `node --version` |
| Python 3.9+ | Both methods | `python --version` |
| MySQL 8.0 | Manual method | `mysql --version` |
| Docker Desktop | Docker method | `docker --version` |

---

# Method 1: Docker (Recommended — Easiest)

> [!TIP]
> Docker handles everything automatically — database, all 7 services, networking. Just 3 commands!

### Step 1: Generate ML Models (One-Time)

The FastText models are too large for Git. Train them locally first:

```powershell
# Install Python dependencies
pip install -r models/teamRecommenderNew/requirements.txt

# Train Team Recommender model (run FROM its directory)
cd d:\Projects\SkillNet\models\teamRecommenderNew
python train_model.py

# Train Project Matcher model (run FROM its directory)
cd d:\Projects\SkillNet\models\projectMatcherNew
python train_model.py
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> You MUST `cd` into each model directory first. The training scripts use relative paths.

### Step 2: Start Everything

```powershell
cd d:\Projects\SkillNet
docker compose up --build -d
```

That's it! Docker will:
- Pull/build all images
- Create a MySQL database with seed data
- Start all 7 services with proper networking
- Handle the startup order automatically

### Step 3: Verify

```powershell
docker compose ps
```

All 7 containers should show `Up`:

| Container | Port | Status |
|-----------|------|--------|
| skillnet-db | 3307 | Up (healthy) |
| skillnet-backend | 5001 | Up |
| skillnet-api-gateway | 5000 | Up |
| skillnet-frontend | 3000 | Up |
| skillnet-team-recommender | 5002 | Up |
| skillnet-project-matcher | 5003 | Up |
| skillnet-recruiter-engine | 5004 | Up |

### Step 4: Open the App

Open **http://localhost:3000** in your browser 🎉

### Docker Commands Reference

```powershell
# Stop all services
docker compose down

# Stop and reset database (full clean restart)
docker compose down -v

# View logs for a specific service
docker compose logs backend
docker compose logs frontend

# Rebuild a single service
docker compose up --build -d backend
```

> [!NOTE]
> If your local MySQL is running on port 3306, Docker uses port **3307** for its MySQL to avoid conflicts. The internal Docker networking still uses 3306 between containers.

